/* All About Prolog */

1. Prolog interpreter is invoked using prolog -i

2. To load a file (my_example.P) ==> [my_example].

3. To make a query:
   a. load the program
   b. then make a query ==> action(car, X).
   c. to continue to make another query use ;

4. To go into a mode to enter facts 
   a. [user].
   b. then put each fact on a line and end with a .
   c. cntrl d (to quit from this mode).
   d. then a query can be entered using the above facts.

5. Programs can be written with rules and facts.

6. To trace the execution of a program, enter trace.

7. To stop enter halt.

